64476009.jpeg\\\" width=\\\"384\\\" \\/><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/td>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t<tr>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<td style=\\\"padding:0cm 0cm 0cm 0cm; background-color:#f7f7f7\\\" valign=\\\"top\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<div style=\\\"border-bottom:solid #f7f7f7 1.0pt; border-top:solid #f7f7f7 1.0pt; border-left:none; border-right:none; padding:9.0pt 0cm 5.0pt 0cm\\\">\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<p class=\\\"ImageCaption\\\" style=\\\"border:none; text-align:center; padding:0cm; margin-bottom:8px\\\"><span style=\\\"font-size:8.5pt\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Times,serif\\\"><span lang=\\\"EN-US\\\" style=\\\"color:black\\\">The Nintendo &quot;flagship&quot; - handheld Game Boy<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/p>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/div>\\r\\n\\t\\t\\t<\\/td>\\r\\n\\t\\t<\\/tr>\\r\\n\\t<\\/tbody>\\r\\n<\\/table>\\r\\n\\r\\n<ol>\\r\\n\\t<li><span style=\\\"font-size:11.5pt\\\"><span style=\\\"line-height:110%\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Times,serif\\\"><b><span lang=\\\"EN-US\\\" style=\\\"color:#e64c4c\\\">Game &amp; Watch<\\/span><\\/b> was Nintendo&#39;s first product offering out-of-home gaming. From 1980 to 1991, over a hundred games were released, gaining great popularity.<\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><span style=\\\"font-size:11.5pt\\\"><span style=\\\"line-height:110%\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Times,serif\\\">In 1989, the original <b><span style=\\\"color:#e64c4c\\\">Game Boy<\\/span><\\/b> was released. The new amazing machine utilized a cartridge system, allowing the users to play a multitude of games of all kinds. This was <span style=\\\"background:#fdfd77\\\"><span style=\\\"color:black\\\">a historical game-changer<\\/span><\\/span>. <\\/span><\\/span><\\/span><\\/li>\\r\\n\\t<li><span style=\\\"font-size:11.5pt\\\"><span style=\\\"line-height:110%\\\"><span style=\\\"font-family:Times,serif\\\">In 2004, Nintendo introduced a new console family called the <b><span style=\\\"color:#e64c4c\\\">Nintendo DS<\\/span><\\/b>. It sported a dual LCD